  "text": "1) Traditional Machine Learning Malware Classifiers: The use of system calls to detect abnormal software behavior was shown in [CITATION_1] . System call pairs (2-grams) from test traces were compared against those in the normal profile. Any system call pair not present in the normal profile is called a mismatch. If the number of system calls with mismatches in their window in any given time frame exceeded a certain threshold, an intrusion was reported.",
